│ ```                                                          │
│                                                              │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                                            │
│                                                              │
│ The crash was caused by a classic use-after-free error       │
│ within the SLP vectorizer's horizontal reduction logic. The  │
│ code was attempting to re-analyze a part of the instruction  │
│ stream that it had just deleted. By removing the redundant   │
│ and incorrect analysis step, we eliminate the access to      │
│ freed memory, thereby fixing the crash. The initial          │
│ vectorization of the reduction is sufficient, and the second │
│ pass was both unnecessary and dangerous.                     │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------              │
